  "prompt": "What do I do when I have a feeling my live-in girlfriend is cheating on me?",
  "response": "Feeling like your partner may be cheating can be distressing. Here are some steps to consider:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to think about why you feel this way. Are there specific behaviors or incidents that have led you to this conclusion?\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: Consider having an honest conversation with your girlfriend about your feelings. Choose a calm and private setting, and express your concerns without being accusatory.\n\n3. **Observe Behavior**: Pay attention to any significant changes in her behavior. While changes can indicate other issues, they might help clarify your feelings.\n\n4. **Avoid Jumping to Conclusions**: Try to remain objective. There may be logical explanations for any changes in her behavior that don't involve infidelity.\n\n5. **Seek Support**: Talk to trusted friends or family members about your feelings. They can provide perspective or advice.\n\n6. **Consider Professional Help**: If you're struggling to cope, consider speaking with a therapist or counselor. They can provide guidance on navigating your feelings and relationship.\n\n7. **Trust Your Instincts**: If you feel strongly that something is wrong, it is important to address that feeling. Trust your instincts, but also remain open-minded.\n\n8. **Plan for the Future**: Think about what you want moving forward. If your suspicions are confirmed, consider what that means for your relationship and what steps you need to take.\n\nIt\u2019s important to approach this situation thoughtfully and carefully to avoid escalating tension in your relationship.",
